===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}}, from {{etyl|ML.}} ''[[instrumentalis]]'', from ''[[instruere]]'' ("to build into, set up, construct, furnish," hence "to train"), from ''[[in-]]'' ("on") + ''[[struere]]'' ("to put together, arrange, pile up, build, construct"), from {{proto|Indo-European|strew-|to spread, to strew}}.

